; Regression test for issue #762: --only doesn't work: does the same as --limit
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/762
;
; The --only flag is a postings predicate that applies *after* calculation
; (and revaluation/rounding adjustments), acting as a display-level filter.
; Unlike --limit (which filters before accumulation), --only keeps all
; postings in the running total but only displays matching ones.
;
; Before the fix, --only behaved identically to --limit for simple register
; reports: both produced a running total of $30.00 for the second posting,
; when --only should produce $20.00 (matching --display behavior, where
; Assets:Cash postings cancel each other out invisibly).

2024/01/01 Payee A
    Expenses:Food    $10.00
    Assets:Cash

2024/01/15 Payee B
    Expenses:Travel  $20.00
    Assets:Cash

; --only filters AFTER accumulation: running total reflects all postings,
; so the second Expenses posting shows running total $20.00, not $30.00.
test reg --only 'account =~ /Expenses/'
24-Jan-01 Payee A               Expenses:Food                $10.00       $10.00
24-Jan-15 Payee B               Expenses:Travel              $20.00       $20.00
end test

; --limit filters BEFORE accumulation: running total includes only matching
; postings, so the second Expenses posting shows running total $30.00.
test reg --limit 'account =~ /Expenses/'
24-Jan-01 Payee A               Expenses:Food                $10.00       $10.00
24-Jan-15 Payee B               Expenses:Travel              $20.00       $30.00
end test

; --display filters at display time (after accumulation), behaving the
; same as --only for this simple case.
test reg --display 'account =~ /Expenses/'
24-Jan-01 Payee A               Expenses:Food                $10.00       $10.00
24-Jan-15 Payee B               Expenses:Travel              $20.00       $20.00
end test
